# Windows-safe bash command formatting

- Do not split bash commands across lines using trailing backslashes (`\`).
- Always write commands as one physical line.
- If a command is getting long, prefer `&&` or `;` separators on one line instead of multiline continuation.

Examples:

```bash
# Bad (line continuation with \)
python script.py \
  --train-size 1500 \
  --valid-size 300

# Good (single line)
python script.py --train-size 1500 --valid-size 300
```
